Vdisk: [History]

   10	                                
   11	                                ;------------------------------------------------------------- Vdisk.mac ------
   12	                                ;
   13	                                ;	VDISK.MAC
   14	                                ;
   15	                                ;	Bondwell 12  Virtual Disk
   16	                                ;
   17	                                ;
   18	                                ;	Copyright (C)	1987	M.J. Moene
   19	                                ;				1098 EC Amsterdam
   20	                                ;
   21	                                ;	Program derived from:
   22	                                ;				Databus, februari 1985
   23	                                ;				Meer performance met uitbreiding opslageenheden.
   24	                                ;				Het aanpassen van CP/M aan een opslageenheid
   25	                                ;				E.L. van 't Hoff
   26	                                ;
   27	                                ;
   28	                                ;	With this program you can install a virtual disk (RAM disk) on your
   29	                                ;	Bondwell 12/14 computer.
   30	                                ;	The virtual disk (VD) uses the additional memory banks 2 & 3 of the
   31	                                ;	standard Bondwell 12/14 computer.  Optionally banks 4..9 can be added
   32	                                ;	with a small hardware extension.
   33	                                ;	Virtual Disk space (Directory + data) ranges from 32 kbyte for a single
   34	                                ;	bank to 256 kbyte for a fully implemented virtual disk. 
   35	                                ;
   36	                                ;
   37	                                ;	Use:
   38	                                ;		D>vdisk [-f]	[]: optional
   39	                                ;
   40	                                ; 		vdisk -f	vdisk format & initialize virtual-drive routines
   41	                                ;		vdisk		initialize virtual-drive routines only
   42	                                ;
   43	                                ;	Note:
   44	                                ;
   45	                                ;	Installing the virtual disk after a cold boot must be done with
   46	                                ;	the '-f' option.
   47	                                ;
   48	                                ;
   49	                                ;	Version         1.8	Errors in comment for modification of 
   50	                                ;	Date	 1988-03-04	computerboard removed (wire cuts, new wires).
   51	                                ;
   52	                                ;	Version		1.7	Old BIOS jump-table in vdbios removed,
   53	                                ;	Date	 1987-02-19	savstk routine shrinked. 
   54	                                ;                               All done to use less space.
   55	                                ;
   56	                                ;	Version		1.6	Read and write routines use a local stack now,
   57	                                ;	Date	 1987-10-14	so programs are allowed to call these routines
   58	                                ;				directly; version 1.5 and before would crash if
   59	                                ;				a program called the read- or write-routine and
   60	                                ;				the stackpointer pointed into memory bank 1,
   61	                                ;				(sp --> address <$8000).
   62	                                ;
   63	                                ;	Version		1.5	Modification description corrected.
   64	                                ;	Date	 1987-02-15	
   65	                                ;
   66	                                ;	Version		1.4	Directory buffer now shared with A: & B:
   67	                                ;	Date	 1987-02-09	  drives. Program doesn't overwrite function
   68	                                ;				  keys anymore ($f6bf..f7b3).
   69	                                ;
   70	                                ;	Version		1.3	Hardware extension extended to give a 
   71	                                ;	Date	 1987-02-02	refreshed A7.
   72	                                ;
   73	                                ;	Version:	1.2	Vdisk without '-F' option: program ends with
   74	                                ;	Date:	 1987-01-20	  warmboot to correctly init. C: drive and
   75	                                ;				  make directory visible again.
   76	                                ;
   77	                                ;	Version:	1.1	Warmboot from VD now logs in on VD again.
   78	                                ;	Date:	 1987-01-20
   79	                                ;
   80	                                ;	Version:	1.0	
   81	                                ;	Date:	 1987-01-20
   82	                                ;
   83	                                ;	Version:	0.0	Setup.
   84	                                ;	Date:	 1987-01-16
   85	                                ;
